  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes. In the United States, key anti-money laundering laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. These laws require financial institutions to:\n\n1. Implement customer identification programs\n2. Report suspicious transactions\n3. Maintain transaction records\n4. Conduct due diligence on customers\n\nPenalties for money laundering can include significant fines and criminal prosecution.",
